{
  "texts": [
    "The probability of the model generating a False Positive is substantially higher (sometimes near twice as likely) than for reliable leftist or center biased publishers.",
    "We conclude that the model tends to confuse articles from reliable right biased publishers with unreliable ones, far beyond what would be considered 'due to chance'.",
    "On the other hand, the model tends to be overly optimistic for center-biased publishers, with lower FP probabilities and a tendency for slightly higher FN probabilities.",
    "An unreliable publisher could therefore escape moderation by limiting its explicit political views.",
    "While this is a relatively unlikely example, as most unreliable publishers are unreliable because of overt extreme political views, it does showcase an important blindspot for these models."
  ]
}